Start with git init, gives you a ./.git/ directiory
Check commits with git status
Add/cache files with git add <file>
Commit added/cached files with git commit -m '-m is a message option'
Look at the software history: git log
^Outputs "commit <giant hex id, commit hash>", author, timestamp, and messages
Using the commit hash, use git checkout <commit hash> -b <new branch name>
Use git branch to see which branches exist (* on current branch)
Compare using git diff HEAD HEAD^
^ means parent. HEAD = head of current branch
./bootstrap
./configure
make
git show <commit hash> >quote-patch.txt to show all changes and put into patch file
patch -p1 < quote-patch.txt
